---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";

const title = "Simplified Rules Overview";
const description = "A clear, beginner-friendly summary of the official One Piece Card Game rules for fast learning and quick reference.";
---

<MainLayout title={title} description={description}>
	<section class="hero">
		<div class="container rules-hero-grid">
			<div class="rules-hero-copy">
				<div class="rules-hero-header">
					<div class="rules-hero-heading">
						<span class="hero-badge">Beginner Guides</span>
						<h1>Simplified Rules Overview</h1>
					</div>
					<div class="rules-hero-cover" aria-hidden="true">
						<img src="/assets/beginner-guides/simplified-rules.png" alt="" loading="eager" />
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="rules-hero-body">
					<p>
						This page is a simplified, accurate summary of the official One Piece Card Game rules. It keeps the
						same structure as the official manuals but focuses on the essentials you need to start playing
						correctly. It does not add strategy or interpretation. If you want the complete, detailed reference,
						use the <a class="inline-link" href="/beginner-guides/complete-rules">Complete One Piece Card Game Rules</a> page.
					</p>
					<p>
						You will learn how to set up a game, what each zone is for, how turns flow, and how combat resolves.
						All terms and timings here come directly from the official rules. This is a practical checklist you
						can keep open while learning your first matches.
					</p>
					<p>
						For deck‑specific learning and improvement, go to <a href="/deck-guides">Deck Guides</a>. For a quick
						view of what is popular in tournaments, use <a href="/meta-analysis">Meta Analysis</a>.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="list-section">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>Quick Setup Checklist</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Each player has 1 Leader, a 50‑card main deck, and a 10‑card DON!! deck.</li>
				<li>Shuffle your main deck and place it in the Deck area.</li>
				<li>Place your Leader face up in the Leader area.</li>
				<li>Decide who goes first with rock‑paper‑scissors; the winner chooses first or second.</li>
				<li>Draw 5 cards. Each player may mulligan once (return all cards, shuffle, draw 5).</li>
				<li>Place Life cards equal to the Leader’s Life value from the top of the deck, face down.</li>
				<li>The first player starts the game.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="list-section">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>Card Types (First Look)</h2>
			<div class="rule-visual-list">
				<div class="rule-visual-item">
					<div class="rule-text">
						Leader cards are your main card. They define your deck colors and Life value, and can have
						effects that impact the game.
					</div>
					<button
						class="card-thumb"
						type="button"
						data-card-preview
						data-full="/Cards/OP01/OP01-003.png"
						data-name="Leader card"
					>
						<img src="/Cards/OP01/OP01-003.png" alt="Leader card example" />
					</button>
				</div>
				<div class="rule-visual-item">
					<div class="rule-text">
						Character cards enter the Character area and can attack. Some Characters have effects, while
						others do not.
					</div>
					<button
						class="card-thumb"
						type="button"
						data-card-preview
						data-full="/Cards/OP01/OP01-054.png"
						data-name="Character card"
					>
						<img src="/Cards/OP01/OP01-054.png" alt="Character card example" />
					</button>
				</div>
				<div class="rule-visual-item">
					<div class="rule-text">
						Event cards are played from hand to activate their effect, then are placed in the trash.
					</div>
					<button
						class="card-thumb"
						type="button"
						data-card-preview
						data-full="/Cards/OP01/OP01-029.png"
						data-name="Event card"
					>
						<img src="/Cards/OP01/OP01-029.png" alt="Event card example" />
					</button>
				</div>
				<div class="rule-visual-item">
					<div class="rule-text">
						Stage cards stay in the Stage area and provide ongoing or repeated effects while in play.
					</div>
					<button
						class="card-thumb"
						type="button"
						data-card-preview
						data-full="/Cards/ST04/ST04-017.png"
						data-name="Stage card"
					>
						<img src="/Cards/ST04/ST04-017.png" alt="Stage card example" />
					</button>
				</div>
				<div class="rule-visual-item">
					<div class="rule-text">
						DON!! cards are the resource you use to play Characters, Stages, and Events. You can also give
						active DON!! to your Leader or Characters to increase power during your turn.
					</div>
					<button
						class="card-thumb"
						type="button"
						data-card-preview
						data-full="/Cards/Don/Don.png"
						data-name="DON!! card"
					>
						<img src="/Cards/Don/Don.png" alt="DON!! card illustration" />
					</button>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="list-section">
		<div class="container board-section">
			<h2>Board Layout</h2>
			<p class="section-note">
				This sample board follows the real One Piece Card Game playmat structure so new players can quickly
				understand where each zone goes.
			</p>
			<figure class="board-figure" aria-label="One Piece Card Game board layout example">
				<div class="playmat">
					<div class="playmat-logo">
						<span>ONE PIECE</span>
						<small>CARD GAME</small>
					</div>
					<div class="zone zone-character">
						<span class="zone-number">1</span>
						<div class="zone-title">CHARACTER AREA</div>
						<ul class="zone-notes">
							<li>You can play up to 5 Character cards.</li>
							<li>Characters cannot attack on the turn they were played.</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="zone zone-life">
						<span class="zone-number">8</span>
						<div class="zone-label zone-label-bottom">LIFE</div>
					</div>
					<div class="playmat-middle">
						<div class="turn-flow">
							<div>Refresh Phase</div>
							<div>Draw Phase</div>
							<div>DON!! Phase</div>
							<div>Main Phase</div>
							<div>End Phase</div>
						</div>
						<div class="zone zone-leader">
							<span class="zone-number">2</span>
							<div class="zone-title zone-title-small">LEADER CARD</div>
						</div>
						<div class="zone zone-stage">
							<span class="zone-number">3</span>
							<div class="zone-title zone-title-small">STAGE CARD</div>
						</div>
						<div class="zone zone-deck">
							<span class="zone-number">4</span>
							<div class="zone-title zone-title-small">DECK</div>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="zone zone-don-deck">
						<span class="zone-number">7</span>
						<div class="zone-title zone-title-small">DON!! DECK</div>
					</div>
					<div class="zone zone-cost">
						<span class="zone-number">6</span>
						<div class="zone-title">COST AREA</div>
					</div>
					<div class="zone zone-trash">
						<span class="zone-number">5</span>
						<div class="zone-title zone-title-small">TRASH</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</figure>
			<ol class="board-legend">
				<li><strong>Character Area:</strong> This is where you play Character cards. You can have up to 5 Characters on the field at a time.</li>
				<li><strong>Leader Card:</strong> This is where you place your Leader card.</li>
				<li><strong>Stage Card:</strong> This is where you play your Stage card. Each player can have only one Stage card on the field at a time.</li>
				<li><strong>Deck:</strong> This is where you place your deck and draw cards from.</li>
				<li><strong>Trash:</strong> This is where you place K.O.'d Characters and used cards.</li>
				<li><strong>Cost Area:</strong> This is where you place DON!! cards. Use the cards here to pay costs or power up for battle.</li>
				<li><strong>DON!! Deck:</strong> This is where you place your DON!! deck. It contains exactly 10 DON!! cards.</li>
				<li><strong>Life Cards:</strong> This is where you place your Life cards.</li>
			</ol>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="list-section">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>Win Conditions</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>You win if the opponent has no Life cards and their Leader takes damage.</li>
				<li>You win if the opponent’s deck reaches 0 cards.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="list-section">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>Turn Flow (Every Turn)</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Refresh Phase: set rested cards to active and return given DON!! to Cost area.</li>
				<li>Draw Phase: draw 1 card (first player skips draw on their first turn).</li>
				<li>DON!! Phase: add 2 DON!! to Cost area (first player adds only 1 on their first turn).</li>
				<li>Main Phase: play cards, give DON!!, activate effects, and attack.</li>
				<li>End Phase: resolve end‑of‑turn effects and pass turn.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="list-section">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>Main Phase Essentials</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Play a Character: place it active, then pay its cost.</li>
				<li>Play a Stage: place it active, then pay its cost. You can control only 1 Stage.</li>
				<li>Play an Event with <img class="keyword-badge" src="/assets/keywords/main.png" alt="Main" />: pay cost, resolve effect, then discard it.</li>
				<li>Give DON!!: move active DON!! to a Leader or Character. Each adds +1000 power during your turn.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="list-section">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>Combat (Simplified)</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Attacks are not allowed on the first turn of the game.</li>
				<li>Declare attack: rest a Leader or active Character and choose a target.</li>
				<li>Block Step: defender may use a <img class="keyword-badge" src="/assets/keywords/blocker.png" alt="Blocker" /> to redirect the attack.</li>
				<li>Counter Step: defender may use <img class="keyword-badge" src="/assets/keywords/counter.png" alt="Counter" /> effects from Characters or Events.</li>
				<li>Damage Step: compare power; if attacker ≥ defender, attacker wins.</li>
				<li>Leader hit: take 1 Life card. Character hit: that Character is KO’d and discarded.</li>
				<li>End of battle: resolve end‑of‑battle effects.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="list-section">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>Life and Trigger</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>When a Leader takes damage, take the top Life card.</li>
				<li>If the Life card has <img class="keyword-badge" src="/assets/keywords/trigger.png" alt="Trigger" />, you may reveal it and resolve the effect instead of adding it to hand.</li>
				<li>You may choose not to activate <img class="keyword-badge" src="/assets/keywords/trigger.png" alt="Trigger" /> and keep the card in hand.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<div class="card-modal" data-modal aria-hidden="true">
		<div class="card-modal-inner" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-label="Card preview">
			<button class="modal-close" type="button" data-close>Close</button>
			<img src="" alt="" data-modal-image />
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="board-modal" data-board-modal aria-hidden="true">
		<div class="board-modal-inner" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-label="Board preview">
			<button class="modal-close" type="button" data-board-close>Close</button>
			<div class="board-modal-stage" data-board-stage></div>
		</div>
	</div>
</MainLayout>

<script>
	const modal = document.querySelector("[data-modal]");
	const modalImage = document.querySelector("[data-modal-image]");
	const closeButton = document.querySelector("[data-close]");
	const boardModal = document.querySelector("[data-board-modal]");
	const boardStage = document.querySelector("[data-board-stage]");
	const boardCloseButton = document.querySelector("[data-board-close]");

	const openModal = (fullUrl, name) => {
		if (!modal || !modalImage) return;
		modalImage.setAttribute("src", fullUrl);
		modalImage.setAttribute("alt", name);
		modal.classList.add("is-open");
		modal.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "false");
	};

	const closeModal = () => {
		if (!modal) return;
		modal.classList.remove("is-open");
		modal.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "true");
	};

	const isMobileBoardView = () => window.matchMedia("(max-width: 720px)").matches;

	const openBoardModal = (figure) => {
		if (!boardModal || !boardStage || !figure) return;
		const clone = figure.cloneNode(true);
		clone.classList.remove("board-preview-trigger");
		clone.removeAttribute("data-board-preview");
		boardStage.innerHTML = "";
		boardStage.append(clone);
		boardModal.classList.add("is-open");
		boardModal.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "false");
	};

	const closeBoardModal = () => {
		if (!boardModal || !boardStage) return;
		boardModal.classList.remove("is-open");
		boardModal.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "true");
		boardStage.innerHTML = "";
	};

	document.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
		const cardButton = event.target.closest("[data-card-preview]");
		if (cardButton) {
			const fullUrl = cardButton.getAttribute("data-full");
			const name = cardButton.getAttribute("data-name") || "Card preview";
			if (fullUrl) openModal(fullUrl, name);
			return;
		}
		const boardFigure = event.target.closest("[data-board-preview]");
		if (boardFigure && isMobileBoardView()) {
			openBoardModal(boardFigure);
			return;
		}
		if (event.target === modal) closeModal();
		if (event.target === boardModal) closeBoardModal();
	});

	closeButton?.addEventListener("click", closeModal);
	boardCloseButton?.addEventListener("click", closeBoardModal);
	window.addEventListener("keydown", (event) => {
		if (event.key === "Escape") closeModal();
		if (event.key === "Escape") closeBoardModal();
	});
</script>

<style>
	.rules-hero-grid {
		display: block;
	}

	.rules-hero-copy {
		max-width: none;
	}

	.rules-hero-header {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(180px, 240px);
		gap: 1.5rem;
		align-items: center;
		max-width: 72rem;
	}

	.rules-hero-heading {
		min-width: 0;
	}

	.rules-hero-body {
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
		max-width: none;
	}

	.rules-hero-cover {
		justify-self: end;
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 240px;
		border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 107, 61, 0.22);
		background:
			radial-gradient(circle at top, rgba(255, 122, 24, 0.16), transparent 58%),
			rgba(12, 17, 30, 0.78);
		box-shadow: var(--shadow);
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.rules-hero-cover img {
		display: block;
		width: 100%;
		aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
		object-fit: cover;
	}

	.section-note {
		color: var(--text-300);
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.board-legend {
		margin: 1.5rem 0 0;
		padding-left: 1.2rem;
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.55rem;
		color: var(--text-200);
		max-width: 72rem;
	}

	.board-section {
		max-width: min(100%, 92rem);
	}

	.board-figure {
		margin: 0;
		padding: 1rem;
		border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		background:
			radial-gradient(circle at top, rgba(255, 122, 24, 0.18), transparent 55%),
			rgba(10, 14, 24, 0.88);
		box-shadow: var(--shadow);
	}

	.playmat {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 12rem minmax(0, 1fr) 12rem;
		grid-template-rows: auto auto auto;
		grid-template-areas:
			"logo character character"
			"life middle middle"
			"dondeck cost trash";
		gap: 1.25rem;
		padding: 1.25rem;
		border-radius: calc(var(--radius-lg) - 4px);
		background:
			radial-gradient(circle at top, rgba(255, 122, 24, 0.16), transparent 34%),
			linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.98), rgba(10, 14, 24, 0.98));
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 122, 24, 0.18);
		box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
	}

	.playmat-logo {
		grid-area: logo;
		align-self: start;
		padding: 0.25rem 0.1rem 0 0.1rem;
		color: var(--text-100);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
	}

	.playmat-logo span {
		display: block;
		font-size: 1.9rem;
		line-height: 0.9;
	}

	.playmat-logo small {
		display: block;
		font-size: 1rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.18em;
		color: var(--text-300);
	}

	.zone {
		position: relative;
		border: 2px solid rgba(255, 122, 24, 0.9);
		border-radius: 0.9rem;
		background:
			linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0)),
			radial-gradient(circle at top, rgba(255, 122, 24, 0.08), transparent 70%),
			rgba(12, 17, 30, 0.9);
		box-shadow:
			inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04),
			0 14px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.24);
		overflow: hidden;
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		text-align: center;
		padding: 1.25rem;
	}

	.zone-number {
		position: absolute;
		top: 0;
		left: 0;
		width: 3.8rem;
		height: 3.8rem;
		display: grid;
		place-items: center;
		background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--accent-2), var(--accent));
		color: #fff;
		font-size: 1.8rem;
		font-weight: 900;
		line-height: 1;
		border-bottom-right-radius: 1rem;
		box-shadow: 0 10px 18px rgba(255, 122, 24, 0.22);
	}

	.zone-title {
		color: var(--text-100);
		font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 1.8vw, 2.6rem);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
		text-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.28);
	}

	.zone-title-small {
		font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 1.3vw, 1.8rem);
	}

	.zone-label-bottom {
		align-self: flex-end;
		font-size: 2rem;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		color: var(--text-100);
		text-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
	}

	.zone-character {
		grid-area: character;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: flex-start;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 0.9rem;
		padding: 4.8rem 1.8rem 1.6rem;
		min-height: 14rem;
	}

	.zone-notes {
		margin: 0;
		padding-left: 1.2rem;
		align-self: flex-start;
		text-align: left;
		color: var(--text-200);
		font-size: 0.98rem;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.zone-life {
		grid-area: life;
		min-height: 23rem;
		align-items: flex-end;
		justify-content: flex-start;
		padding: 1.2rem;
	}

	.playmat-middle {
		grid-area: middle;
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 12rem repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1rem;
		align-items: stretch;
	}

	.turn-flow {
		grid-column: 1;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 0.55rem;
		padding: 0.4rem 0;
	}

	.turn-flow div {
		width: 100%;
		padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
		border-radius: 999px;
		background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(71, 85, 105, 0.95), rgba(51, 65, 85, 0.95));
		color: #f8fafc;
		font-weight: 800;
		text-align: center;
		position: relative;
		box-shadow: 0 8px 18px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.28);
		font-size: 0.95rem;
	}

	.turn-flow div:not(:last-child)::after {
		content: "";
		position: absolute;
		left: 50%;
		top: calc(100% + 0.12rem);
		width: 2px;
		height: 0.45rem;
		background: #475569;
		transform: translateX(-50%);
	}

	.zone-leader,
	.zone-stage,
	.zone-deck,
	.zone-don-deck,
	.zone-cost,
	.zone-trash {
		min-height: 12rem;
	}

	.zone-leader {
		grid-column: 2;
	}

	.zone-stage {
		grid-column: 3;
	}

	.zone-deck {
		grid-column: 4;
	}

	.zone-don-deck {
		grid-area: dondeck;
	}

	.zone-cost {
		grid-area: cost;
	}

	.zone-trash {
		grid-area: trash;
	}

	@media (max-width: 1100px) {
		.playmat {
			grid-template-columns: 9.5rem minmax(0, 1fr) 9.5rem;
		}

		.playmat-middle {
			grid-template-columns: 9.5rem repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 920px) {
		.playmat {
			grid-template-columns: 9.5rem minmax(0, 1fr) 9.5rem;
		}

		.playmat-middle {
			grid-template-columns: 9.5rem repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
			gap: 1rem;
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 620px) {
		.playmat-logo span {
			font-size: 1.45rem;
		}

		.playmat-logo small {
			font-size: 0.8rem;
		}

		.zone-number {
			width: 3rem;
			height: 3rem;
			font-size: 1.35rem;
		}

		.zone-title {
			font-size: 1.3rem;
		}

		.zone-title-small {
			font-size: 1.05rem;
		}

		.zone-label-bottom {
			font-size: 1.45rem;
		}

		.zone-character {
			padding: 3.7rem 1rem 1rem;
		}

		.zone-notes {
			font-size: 0.85rem;
		}

		.turn-flow div {
			font-size: 0.85rem;
		}
	}

	.rule-visual-list {
		display: grid;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}

	.rule-visual-item {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 1.2rem;
		padding: 0.8rem 1rem;
		border-radius: var(--radius-md);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		background: rgba(12, 17, 30, 0.6);
